ZCZC OE80
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 232300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE
1023HPA IS EXP TO LIE OVER THE SERN BRITISH ISLES AND
THE NEAR CONTINENT. BY EARLY SATURDAY THIS HIGH BECOMES
ESTABLISHED OVER SERN UK INTSF TO 1028HPA AS A LOW
PRESSURE CENTRE 980 LIES SE OF ICELAND. THIS LOW CENTRE
IS EXP TO TRACK NE ACROSS ICELAND CLEARING PORTPATRICK
THROUGH SUNDAY. MEANWHILE THE HIGH PRESSURE REMAINS OVER
THE UK DRIFTING SLWY E TO LIE IN THE SERN N SEA BY
SUNDA WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE OF AROUND 1035. FURTHER LOW
PRESSURE CENTRES TRACK N TO THE W OF THE UK THROUGH
MONDAY BUT ARE HELD TO THE W OF 15 W BY THE HIGH
PRESSURE. STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY TO AFFECT THE W OF THE
AREA ON SATURDAY PERHAPS APPROACHING GALE FORCE FOR A
TIME ACROSS ROCKALL AND BAILEY LATER BEFORE CLEARING TO
THE N EARLY SUNDAY. FURTHER STRG WINDS MAY THEN AFFECT
MUCH OF THE AREA AGAIN AT TIMES THROUGH MONDAY.
